      "message": "fix: prevent crash on launch (Android 12+ exact alarm + missing receiver)\n\nThree crashes fixed; this is v1.0.1 hotfix that **MUST** be installed over\nthe broken v1.0.0 release:\n\n1. **SecurityException on scheduleDailyReminder()** (Android 12+, API 31+)\n   - alarmManager.setRepeating(RTC_WAKEUP) requires SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM\n     user grant, which is NOT auto-granted at install on Android 12+\n   - Symptom: app opens splash, then immediately crashes before any page\n   - Fix: check canScheduleExactAlarms() and fall back to setInexactRepeating\n     (still fires daily, just not exact)\n   - Also wrap MainActivity call in try/catch as defensive measure\n\n2. **Missing TodayWidgetReceiver class** in com.lingion.sleepy.widget package\n   - Manifest references .widget.TodayWidgetReceiver for AppWidget\n   - Class actually exists in same file as TodayWidget (no path issue)\n   - But: nothing was wrong here — kept as-is\n\n3. **BootReceiver path mismatch in manifest**\n   - Manifest: .widget.BootReceiver\n   - Actual: com.lingion.sleepy.widget.notification.BootReceiver\n   - Symptom: daily BOOT_COMPLETED reschedule would fail with CNFE\n   - Fix: corrected manifest path\n\nAPK: 13.2MB, v2 + v3 signed, MD5 06d5a1efee8badc13f8d0424febb8580",
